n1. **Social Media Management and Public Relations Support**\n\n    This includes PR strategy, full social media management, and a marketing manager role, who would function as a head of marketing or fractional CMO. This person would be responsible for communicating with and interacting with the DAO, managing marketing sprints and larger campaigns, and ensuring the success of the engagement.\n\n    Pricing: **$20,000 per month.**\n\n2. **Social Media Management, Public Relations Support, Long-Form Content and Design Services**\n\n    This would include everything in option 1, plus bi-weekly blog posts and full design services for both static and video content.\n\n    Pricing: **$25,000 per month.**\n\nThe DAO can choose one of these two options if Scrib3 is approved.\n\nBoth options have an operational timeline of **1 year**.\n\n### Radarblock\nRadarblock’s proposal includes:\n* Growth Package (Twitter and PR): **$15,000 per month**\n* Twitter Account Management: **$12,000 per month**\n* PR Account Management: **$10,000 per month**\n\nTotal Cost: **$37,000 per month**\n\n**Note**: Costs exclude individual KOL and selected PR outlet expenses, which are payable directly to the concerned parties without any markup from Radarblock.\n\nThis proposal has an operational timeline of **four months**.\n\n## Voting\nFor RFP-30, the DAO members will participate in a [ranked-choice voting process](https://docs.snapshot.org/user-guides/proposals/voting-types#ranked-choice-voting-instant-runoff-voting). The agency with the highest cumulative preference across all votes will be selected for the marketing and PR activities of Radiant. Members are asked to rank the following options based on their preference:\n\n* **Radarblock:** Rank this option based on your preference for Radarblock.\n\n* **Scrib3:** Rank this option based on your preference for Scrib3.\n* **Serotonin:** Rank this option based on your preference for Serotonin.\n* **Against RFP-30:** Select this option if you prefe