      "content": "## Abstract\n\nRFP-21 seeks consensus from Radiant DAO stakeholders on the airdrop distribution mechanics between 6-month and 12-month locks for the ARB allocation received through RFP-18. \n\n\n## Motivation\n\n\n### Context\n\nAs per [RFP-18](https://dao.radiant.capital/#/proposal/0x098762ed9d2d959596d642ea3180243fa7cb6ae7a85a58145e296c16d559351d), the ARB allocation of 3,348,026 tokens received by the Radiant DAO treasury was earmarked to incentivize engagement and liquidity within the Radiant ecosystem. The proposal ratified allocating up to 40% of these tokens as an airdrop to new 6-month and 12-month dLP lockers.\n\nTo enact this, an airdrop window was implemented between **May 17 17:00 UTC** and **July 17 18:00 UTC**. The block range is as follows:\n\n \n\n**ARB**: [#91675675](https://arbiscan.io/block/91675675) - [#112210150](https://arbiscan.io/block/112210150)\n\n**BNB**: [#28294775](https://www.bscscan.com/block/28294775) - [#30048350](https://www.bscscan.com/block/30048350)\n\n### Qualifying Wallets\n\nAll wallets which locked or relocked dLP within the block heights above on either Arbitrum & BNB Chain are initially eligible for the airdrop.\n\nTo further refine the allocation strategy, RFP-21 aims to determine:\n\n1. Distribution ratio between 6-month and 12-month locks\n\n2. Appropriate airdrop cutoffs for dLP locked within the eligible airdrop window\n\n\n## Key Terms\n\n\n\n* **Airdrop window:** The period of time between **May 17 2023, 17:00 UTC** and **July 17 2023, 18:00 UTC**.\n* **ARB:** The governance token of the Arbitrum Foundation.\n* **dLP:** Dynamic Liquidity Providers within the Radiant ecosystem.\n\n## Specifications\n\n### Weight Options\n\n**2.5x weight:** The airdrop allocation to 12-month locks would be **2.5 times** that of 6-month locks. This is in line with the current APR multiplier weight respective to 6-month and 12-month locks.\n\n**3x weight:** The airdrop allocation to 12-month locks would be **three times** that of 6-month locks. This option rewards long-term commitment to the protocol. \n\n### Airdrop Claim\nAll qualifying locks on Arbitrum and BNB Chain networks are eligible, but please note that the airdrop will only be claimable on Arbitrum.\n\n\n## Steps to Implement\n\n* _(completed)_ Airdrop UI\n* _(completed)_ User addresses sortable by:\n    * List of lockers on both chains\n    * Amount locked per duration for each chain\n* Apply allocation weight from RFP-21\n* Parse into final userlist for smart contract linkup\n* Testing & deployment\n\n\n## Overall Cost/Impact\n\nMinimal. ARB allocation has already been earmarked by the DAO.\n\n\n## Timeline\n\n**21-Jul – 27-Jul:** Create smart contract with placeholder weighting formula & ARB values\n\n**24-Jul – 29-Jul:** RFP-21 to determine airdrop weighting\n\n**29-Jul – 30-Jul:** Apply final weighting and formula to userlist; testing & staging \n\n**30-Jul:** Deploy\n\n_Note: timeline is estimated and subject to change based on any unforeseen issues._\n\n\n## Voting\n\n**A:** In favor of **2.5x** weight between 6 month and 12 month eligible locks\n\n**B:** In favor of **3x** weight between 6 month and 12 month eligible locks\n\n**Against:** Against implementation of all options proposed in RFP-21\n\n**Abstain:** Undecided, but contributing to quorum.",
